/*
===========================================================
TITLE
===========================================================
Copy List with Random Pointer (Deep Copy using O(1) Extra Space)

===========================================================
PROBLEM STATEMENT
===========================================================
You are given a linked list where each node contains:
• `val`    → value of the node
• `next`   → pointer to the next node
• `random` → pointer to any node in the list or null

Your task is to create a **deep copy** of the linked list such that:
• Each node in the copied list is a new node
• `next` and `random` pointers replicate the original structure
• No pointer in the copied list refers to any node in the original list

===========================================================
PROBLEM RESOURCE (links)
===========================================================
https://leetcode.com/problems/copy-list-with-random-pointer/

===========================================================
INTUITION
===========================================================
The challenge is copying the `random` pointer efficiently without
using extra space (like a HashMap).

Key observation:
If every original node is followed immediately by its copied node,
then:
• The copied node of `curr` is `curr.next`
• The copied node of `curr.random` is `curr.random.next`

This allows us to set random pointers **without extra memory**.

===========================================================
APPROACH
===========================================================
We solve this problem in **three passes**:

PASS 1: Clone nodes and interleave them
---------------------------------------
• For each original node, create its copy
• Insert the copied node just after the original node

PASS 2: Assign random pointers to copied nodes
-----------------------------------------------
• For original node `curr`:
  copied node = `curr.next`
  copied.random = `curr.random.next`

PASS 3: Separate original and copied lists
-------------------------------------------
• Restore the original list
• Extract the copied list as a separate deep copy

===========================================================
EXAMPLE
===========================================================
Original List:
1 → 2 → 3
|    |    |
v    v    v
3    1   null   (random pointers)

After PASS 1:
1 → 1' → 2 → 2' → 3 → 3'

After PASS 2:
1'.random → 3'
2'.random → 1'
3'.random → null

After PASS 3:
Original: 1 → 2 → 3
Copied:   1' → 2' → 3'

===========================================================
DRY RUN
===========================================================
Input:
1 → 2
random: 1→2, 2→1

PASS 1:
1 → 1' → 2 → 2'

PASS 2:
1'.random = 2'
2'.random = 1'

PASS 3:
Original restored: 1 → 2
Copied list:       1' → 2'

===========================================================
KEY POINTS
===========================================================
• No HashMap is used
• Each node is copied exactly once
• Random pointers resolved using structural placement
• Original list structure is restored

===========================================================
TIME COMPLEXITY
===========================================================
O(n)
- Three linear traversals of the list

===========================================================
SPACE COMPLEXITY
===========================================================
O(1)
- No extra data structures used (excluding output list)

===========================================================
SPECIAL NOTES FOR LOGIC
===========================================================
• Copied node of `curr` is always `curr.next`
• Copied node of `curr.random` is `curr.random.next`
• Interleaving nodes is the core trick
• This is the most optimal and interview-preferred solution
===========================================================
*/

/*
// Definition for a Node.
class Node {
    int val;
    Node next;
    Node random;

    public Node(int val) {
        this.val = val;
        this.next = null;
        this.random = null;
    }
}
*/

class Solution {

    public Node copyRandomList(Node head) {

        // Edge case: empty list
        if (head == null) return head;

        Node curr = head;

        // -------------------------------------------------
        // PASS 1: Create copied nodes and interleave them
        // -------------------------------------------------
        while (curr != null) {

            Node currNext = curr.next;        // Store next original node
            curr.next = new Node(curr.val);  // Create copied node
            curr.next.next = currNext;       // Insert copied node after original

            curr = currNext;                 // Move to next original node
        }

        // -------------------------------------------------
        // PASS 2: Assign random pointers to copied nodes
        // -------------------------------------------------
        curr = head;

        while (curr != null && curr.next != null) {

            if (curr.random == null) {
                curr.next.random = null;     // If original random is null
            } else {
                // copied.random = copied version of original.random
                curr.next.random = curr.random.next;
            }

            curr = curr.next.next;           // Move to next original node
        }

        // -------------------------------------------------
        // PASS 3: Separate original and copied lists
        // -------------------------------------------------
        Node newHead = head.next;             // Head of copied list
        curr = head;
        Node newCurr = newHead;

        while (curr != null && newCurr != null) {

            // Restore original list next pointer
            curr.next = (curr.next == null) ? null : curr.next.next;

            // Fix copied list next pointer
            newCurr.next = (newCurr.next == null) ? null : newCurr.next.next;

            curr = curr.next;                // Move original pointer
            newCurr = newCurr.next;          // Move copied pointer
        }

        // Return head of deep-copied list
        return newHead;
    }
}
